------- INSTALLING tcpdump -------------
sudo apt-get install tcpdump apparmor-utils
sudo aa-disable /usr/sbin/tcpdump
 ----> Not always necessary: see documentation.
 	In my case: sudo aa-disable /usr/bin/tcpdump
 	Use the following to find where tcpdump was installed:
 		dpkg -L tcpdump

sudo apt-get install tcpdump
 ----> Already installed.
sudo groupadd pcap
sudo usermod -a -G pcap cuckoo
 ---> (with my username): sudo usermode -a -G pcap v
sudo chgrp pcap /usr/bin/tcpdump
sudo setcap cap_net_raw,cap_net_admin=eip /usr/bin/tcpdump
-----> Offical cuckoo's documentation: /usr/sbin/tcpdump
	VERIFY RESULTS:
	$ getcap /usr/bin/tcpdump
	/usr/sbin/tcpdump = cap_net_admin,cap_net_raw+eip


